input: [15,2,-2,-8,1,7,10,23]
output : 5
sum of 2,-2,-8,1,7 =0
if [2,4,8] is input then output =0

logic:

same numbers of sum occurs means inbetween elements sum =0

use map to store the sum and index
if sum == 0 , find the max length with index of array
in map , if we find the exising sum , then we can use for finding max len
  becox same num exist again means then inbetween element add gives 0 
  so i-map.(previousSameSum) gives elements between them which sum =0
  dont update map for this case since later if we find also it will be helpful



class Solution {
    int maxLength(int arr[]) {
        // code here
        int sum= 0;
        int maxLen=0;
        Map<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i=0; i<arr.length;i++){
             sum=sum+  arr[i];
             if(sum==0){
                 maxLen= i+1;
             }
             if(map.containsKey(sum)){
                 int prevIndex= map.get(sum);
                     maxLen= Math.max(maxLen, i-prevIndex);
     
             }else{
                 map.put(sum,i);
             }
            
            
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
